oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Reflections of a Female School Executive
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Gipson, Willa
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Women rising in school leadership positions is becoming more of a reality than in years past. I believe this accomplishment is attributed to women taking more control of their careers instead of acting in a passive role waiting to be selected or appointed.
oai_dc:dc.dc:publisher: Education Leadership Research Center, Texas A&M University
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Advancing Women in Leadership Journal; Vol. 2, No. 2 = No. 5 (1999 Spring)
